{
  "summary": "This text is a theological reflection on the role of the Jewish people in the crucifixion of Jesus, as predicted by the prophets Jeremiah and Isaiah. The text describes how the Jews called out for the crucifixion of Jesus to Pontius Pilate, leading to their downfall and the destruction of Jerusalem. The author interprets historical events as a consequence of the Jewish people's rebellion against God, supported by biblical prophecies. This interpretation includes the aftermath of the crucifixion, where the Jewish people's own declaration of responsibility for Jesus' blood led to the Roman destruction of Jerusalem and suffering of future generations.",
  "keywords": ["Anti-Judaism", "Vengeance", "Typology"]
